# Cursor Rules for receipt-ui

## Project Overview
Receipt tracking Telegram Mini App with React 19, TypeScript, Vite, and n8n backend.

## Commands
- `npm run dev` — Start Vite dev server (mock API by default)
- `npm run build` — Type-check + production build
- `npm run preview` — Preview production build
- No test/lint configured. TypeScript strict mode catches issues.

## Code Style (STRICT)
- **NO semicolons** — ever (JS, TS, JSX, CSS)
- **Single quotes** for strings and JSX attributes
- **2-space indentation**
- **NO trailing commas** in objects/arrays
- Line length < 120 chars; break long JSX onto multiple lines
- Currency: Russian ruble (₽) after amount: `{value.toFixed(2)} ₽`

## TypeScript
- `strict: true`, `verbatimModuleSyntax`, `noUnusedLocals`, `noUnusedParameters`
- Use `import type` for type-only imports
- Prefer `interface` for objects, `type` for unions/literals
- No `any` — use `unknown` (exception: Recharts props may need `as any`)
- Dates are ISO strings (`YYYY-MM-DD`), not `Date` objects
- `Receipt.receiptDate` is optional — guard with `item.receiptDate ? ... : ''`

## Naming
- Components: PascalCase (`ReceiptList`)
- Hooks: camelCase with `use` prefix (`useReceipts`)
- Functions/variables: camelCase
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- CSS classes: kebab-case, BEM-like (`.list-entry`, `.list-entry-label`)
- Files: PascalCase for components, camelCase for utils/hooks

## Imports
- Relative imports without extension: `import { x } from '../types'`
- Group: React/hooks first, then local modules, then types
- Type imports: `import type { X }` or inline `import { type X }`

## Architecture
- Single n8n webhook POST with `{ action, payload, auth }`
- `Content-Type: text/plain` to avoid CORS preflight
- 6 actions: `list`, `detail`, `create`, `update`, `delete`, `stats`
- Mock mode: `WEBHOOK_URL='/mock'`
- Auth: Telegram initData HMAC validation
- GitHub Pages deployment with `base: '/receipt-ui/'`
- `axios` is unused — do not reintroduce

## CSS
- Single `src/styles.css` — no CSS modules or CSS-in-JS
- Mobile-first, no media queries (Telegram Mini App is mobile-only)
- Component-prefixed class names (`.receipt-list`, `.detail-item`)

## n8n Node Scripts (n8n/nodes/*.js)
- Same style: no semicolons, 2-space indent, single quotes
- Use `$input.all()`, `$input.first()`, `$env.VAR`
- Return `[{ json: { ... } }]` from Code nodes
- All SQL uses parameterized queries (`$1`, `$2`)
- Rate limiting: 60 req/min per userId
